# Privacy Policy — CookieCut

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

CookieCut is a Chrome extension that automatically declines non-essential cookies on websites you visit. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data Collected

CookieCut stores the following data **locally in your browser only**:

- A count of how many cookie banners have been declined
- A log of the most recent 50 decline events, including the website hostname, the consent platform detected, and the time of the decline

This data is used solely to display stats in the extension popup.

## Data Storage

All data is stored using Chrome's `storage.local` API. It never leaves your browser and is not accessible to any website or third party.

## Data Sharing

No data is collected, transmitted, or shared with any external server, service, or third party.

## Permissions

- **storage** — used to save decline stats locally in your browser
- **host_permissions (`<all_urls>`)** — required to run the content script on every page so cookie banners can be detected and declined

## Changes to This Policy

This policy may be updated occasionally. The latest version will always be available at this URL.

